      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "WASHINGTON. May 13.-The\nprosecution in the Ballinger case\nturned the investigation from Alas\nkan coal lands questions to probe\nof the restoration to entry of water\npower sites under the Ballinger re-\ngime. Attorney George Horton Pep\nper. personal representative of Gift\nford Pinchot, forced Secretary Bal\nlinger to admit that he had not\nmade a close study of reclamation.\n\n\n1t became apparent, from Pep\nper's questions that he sought to\ndefend Director Newell and Chief\nEngineer, Davis of the reclamation\nservice from the previous charges\nof Ballinger."
    }
